<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-08-12T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-08-12T11:00:00-05:00" n="640" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6359 Wolfram Ore/13: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China (<persName type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-12T12:00:00-04:00">August 12,
                                1933—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>281. Your 657, August 9, 9 a.m.<note n="10" xml:id="d640fn10">Not
                                printed.</note> In conversations in New York on August 6 and 7 with
                            Soong, officer of the Department took occasion to comment adversely on
                            the grant of a monopoly for export of wolfram. Soong expressed the view
                            that the principle involved in the action taken by Chinese authorities
                            was wrong and said he would see what he could do about rectifying the
                            situation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>